CSS Selector (Cascading style sheet) it is another way of locating elements on the web page

Syntax:
tagname[attribute = 'attribute value']
button[type = 'submit']

CSS does not give an opportunity to locate the element by its text

Shortcuts for CSS:

shortcut for ClassName -- "."
Syntax:tagname.classNameValue
Example:input.button

Shortcut for ID -- '#'
Syntax:tagname#IDValue
example:input#twotabsearchtextbox

contains() method in css:
*symbol represents contains method
tagname[attribute * = 'attribute value']
Example: inpute[placeholder * = 'Email']
inpute[placeholder * = 'phone']

starts-with method in css:
^ (circumflex) symbol represents starts with method
tagname[attribute ^ = 'starting attribute value']
inpute[type ^ = 'pass']

end-with method in css:
$ symbol represents ends-with method in css:
tagname[attribute $ = 'ending attribute value']
img[src $ = 'syntax.png']


Xpath vs CSS
--CSS cannot locate the elements by text whereas Xpath can
--no ends-with method in Xpath
--CSS faster than Xpath
--CSS has shortcuts
--no advanced CSS
--CSS has more simple syntax than Xpath


WebElements Commands:
consists of several methods where we can perform on action and get the element state on the webpage

isEnabled()--boolean value
isDisplayed()--boolean value
isSelected()--boolean value
clear()-- void
getText()--String
getAttribute()--String value
submit()-- void